entry.title: Flood Advisory issued February 6 at 8:11AM PST until February 6 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
entry.summary:
* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.
* WHERE...Los Angeles County and eastern portions of Ventura County.
* WHEN...Until 1000 AM PST.
* IMPACTS...Widespread roadway and small stream flooding will continue across the advisory area through this morning. In addition, there will be the threat of debris flows, as well as additional rock and mudslide activity, especially in the mountains and canyon roadways.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 805 AM PST, Doppler radar continued to indicate light to moderate rainfall with embedded heavier showers across the advisory area. The heaviest rainfall was located over eastern Los Angeles County stretching from Norwalk and La Mirada into the San Gabriel Valley. This will add to the flooding, debris flow, and mudslide concerns this morning. Rainfall rates between 0.25 and 0.50 inch per hour are expected at times, with local rates up to between 0.60 and 0.80 inch per hour possible near heavier showers and any thunderstorms. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... entry.title: Child Abduction Emergency issued February 6 at 8:49AM MST by NWS Great Falls MT
entry.summary:
CAEMT
THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE MONTANA DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE.
The Missing Endangered Person Advisory for Josiah Killsnight has been upgraded to an AMBER Alert. AMBER Alert issued on behalf of BIA Northern Cheyenne Law Enforcement. Josiah Killsnight has gone missing from Lame Deer on February 5, 2024. Josiah was home at his grandmothers residence with a high fever. He was taken, on foot, from the residence by Kathryn Pretty On Top around 11:20am. She is not related to the child and does not have permission to be with him. She has no vehicle but may have gotten a ride to Billings and both Kathryn and Josiah are believed to be in the Billings area now. Josiah is a 9 year old Native American male with black eyes and black hair. He is 3 feet 10 inches tall and 96 pounds. Kathryn is a 50 year old Native American female with brown eyes and brown hair. Winds gusting to 60 mph and periods of blizzard conditions and freezing rain or sleet are expected over the Yukon Delta and St Lawrence Island with this storm from this afternoon through Thursday. This will bring water levels up 2 to 3 feet from the Bering Strait south Wednesday through Thursday, which could cause water to seep up onto the ice along the coast on Wednesday into Thursday. No flooding is expected, but this could affect the trails that cross ice near the coast from the Bering Strait south.
